# Modeling Explorative Scenarios in Hub:
    - 1. Unstructured Creative Work
        Writing a novel, designing a brand, composing music
        Why Hub struggles: No signal triggers this. No "request." No entity to operate on. The work is the creation, not a response to a scenario.
    - 2. Exploratory Research
        Scientific research, market research, open-ended investigation
        Why Hub struggles: No signal says "research this now." Outcomes are emergent, not predefined. Can't define a scenario for unknown discoveries.
    - 3. Pure Ideation/Brainstorming
        Strategy workshops, innovation sessions
        Why Hub struggles: Deliberately unstructured. No scenario, no SOPs, no defined outcome. Value is in the divergence, not convergence.
    - 4. Relationship-Intensive Information Work
        Sales relationship building, negotiation, mentoring
        Why Hub struggles: Highly relational, depends on human chemistry. Can't systematize trust-building into procedures.
    - 5. Real-Time Crisis Decisions
        Emergency response, novel crises, unprecedented situations
        Why Hub struggles: No pre-existing scenario. No time for systematic processing. Requires improvisation, not procedure.
    - 6. Personal Knowledge Management
        How individuals organize their thoughts, note-taking, personal systems
        Why Hub struggles: Deeply idiosyncratic. Not collaborative. Not systematizable by an external platform.
    - 7. Informal Coordination
        Slack threads, hallway conversations, ad-hoc emails
        Why Hub struggles: No formal signal. No defined outcome. No entity. Work happens in the interstices.